data.title: 608 SW 11th St, Oklahoma City, OK 73109
data.meta_description: Zillow has 50 photos of this $725,000 5 beds, 4 baths, 3,298 Square Feet single family home located at 608 SW 11th St, Oklahoma City, OK 73109 built in 2021. MLS #1121836.
data.text: Discover the unique charm of this custom-built five-bedroom home, located just steps away from Downtown Oklahoma City, National Blue Ribbon Schools award winner John Rex Charter Schools, and Lower Scissortail Park! From the large covered front porch, step into a well-designed and spacious open floor plan boasting 10-foot ceilings and hardwood floors throughout. Expansive windows in the first living area flood the space with natural light. In the well-appointed kitchen, you'll find granite countertops, a beautiful tile backsplash, under-cabinet lighting, custom cabinetry extending to the ceiling, a breakfast bar, stainless steel appliances including a double oven and beverage fridge, and a dedicated pantry. Serving as the heart of the home, the dining space is highlighted by a designer chandelier, built-in cabinetry flanking an oversized banquet, and additional storage in the bench. A half bath for guests and large sliding doors that overlook the back deck and yard enhance the second living area. On the second level, discover a third living space, all bedrooms, full bathrooms, and a convenient utility room. The oversized primary suite includes a private patio and a luxurious ensuite bathroom with a custom vanity with double sinks, quartz countertops, a soaking tub, a walk-in closet, and a walk-in shower with designer tile and two shower heads. Two secondary bedrooms share a Jack-and-Jill bathroom that provides two individual sinks for storage and convenience. Additional great closet space is found in the two bedrooms that share the hall bathroom with custom hall storage between. A detached two-car garage includes an above bonus space, roughed in with electrical and plumbing, ready for you to finish to your liking. Enjoy quick access to John Rex Charter School, Lower Scissortail Park, Skydance Bridge, Myriad Gardens, Paycom Center, OKC Convention Center, Oklahoma River, a vast biking and running trail system, and all the other amenities that epitomize downtown living.
